One thing to do is to check your transaction history; the screenshot you're showing is not that.  Go to scan.bittensor.com or taostats.io and simply search on your address.  You can double-check your transaction history to see what's been happening. 

If a transaction related to staking failed, for example, you'll see that there.

You should also be able to see the current status of your account pulled from on-chain data.

If you are using the Chrome Bittensor Wallet extension and the extension isn't reflecting this, try clearing your cache, completely restarting Chrome, and starting back up again.  The balance of free vs. staked tokens on the extension should reflect what you see on Taostats, though bear in mind that the extension will round up to the nearest two decimal places so it may not be exactly the same.

Also: if the validator to whom you delegated stake has changed (their hotkey changed, they became inactive, they became the childkey of someone else), the Chrome extension (and iOS Bittensor Wallet application) will not reflect this at present.

If this is the case in your situation, you have a couple of options:

1) Wait for Tensora to update the Chrome extension/iOS Application to be released, which should fix this option.  I can't tell you when this will happen.

2) Go to Taostats.io and use it as your interface.  Connect with your Chrome extension as the wallet and you should be able to find your stake and unstake it.
